Trophies.Title: Sigil Of Light

Trophies.Title: Greetings To Fairlight
Trophies.Description: Fairlight is an old group with a lot of members from all over Europe. They've managed to be on top for the past 20 years. Their fresh demo selection has won many different awards for the hi-end machines and also for old-school ones including scene.org award in 4kb, 64kb and demo category.

Trophies.Title: Greetings To Sunflower
Trophies.Description: Sunflower is an old group that brought new trends to the demoscene in the beginning of accelerated era.  Their demos seem to not suffer from time. This is due to their abstract style and very sophisticated music.  The group was formed from very experienced sceners and project "Sunflower" survived for only two years (1999-2001). We all hope that they will make a massive comeback.

Trophies.Title: Greetings To Still
Trophies.Description: Still is a relatively new group formed by ex-members of Bauknecht, lkcc and "Haujobb". Their first productions were released in 2007 but have already received interest and critical acclaim within the demoscene.

Trophies.Title: Greetings To Farbrausch
Trophies.Description:
Farbrausch is a demogroup famous for using procedural techniques for creating textures, scenes, and animations in their productions. "Werkzeug" which is their demotool, successfully started a new era of tools, separating coders from artists, thus speeding up production process. Together with "Werkzeug" came V2, a high-quality software synthesizer that was already adopted by other groups respecting its values. Farbrausch is mostly known for
"Candytron", "The produkkt", "The Popular Demo" and rece

Trophies.Title: Greetings To The Black Lotus
Trophies.Description: The Black Lotus is an old Amiga group with a very distinctive, monumental style, influencing other groups including Plastic. They've managed to beat 2 Ghz computers with a classic 66 Mhz Amiga and a demo called "Starstruck".

Trophies.Title: Greetings To Conspiracy
Trophies.Description: Conspiracy is a Hungarian group that specializes in creating 64-kilobyte intros. As the first group in demoscene history, they've managed to show their real-time production "Chaos Theory" together with other offline, pre-processed animations at SIGGRAPH 2007. This intro has also received a scene.org award.

Trophies.Title: Greetings To RGBA
Trophies.Description: RGBA is a Spanish group known mostly for their 64-kilobyte and their recent 4-kilobyte productions. They are also well known for breaking the mold in 4-kilobyte graphics. Plastic is especially dedicated to sending their greetings to RGBA for their remake of "195/95" demo.

Trophies.Title: Greetings To MFX
Trophies.Description: Mfx demos are known for their distinctive, mostly experimental style, focusing on building a specific dark atmosphere. Even if they prefer the form over content, their demos often visualize a concept or short story. Mfx members can be found also in different groups like Kewlers or Synesthetics. Mfx has been awarded with many awards including the scene.org award for Most Original Concept in a Demo called "The Ballet Dancer".

Trophies.Title: Greetings To Andromeda Software Development
Trophies.Description: Andromeda Software Development is a demogroup with an extremely distinctive style. Their demos featured dynamic coherent flows of abstract visual elements subtly blending into each other in various and unexpected ways. They have won many demoscene awards including Best Demo of the Year 2007 for "Lifeforce" and Best Demo of 2005 for "Planet Risk".

Trophies.Title: Greetings To Madwizards
Trophies.Description: Madwizards is an old group originating out of Poland best known for their accelerated Amiga productions. They've managed to invent their own abstract style while mixing real-time effects together with still post-processed photography. In their most recent production "Senzala", they went back to the roots developing on classic Amiga.

Trophies.Title: Dressed in Epic
Trophies.Description: Loot as many items as you can to eventually find some Epic stuff with better stats. The whole set consists an epic weapon, shield, armor and helmet. You can keep those items after the game is over, so loosing a game does not mean that you have to start to collect the set from the beginning!

Trophies.Title: Dragonskin scarf
Trophies.Description:
Travel through three areas: the Haunted Mill, the Forest and the Dungeon to encounter no less than 12 monsters! Defeat them all and shoot the Loot hole to begin the fight against the giant Random Dragon.
This trophy is for those who can defeat the mighty beast.

Trophies.Title: Letter from Mom
Trophies.Description: Lock three balls and start You Have Mail Multiball on the Plants vs. Zombies table.

Trophies.Description: Confront Dr. Zomboss and triumph over his giant Zombot on the Plants vs. Zombies table.

Trophies.Description: Set the sign of the Fantastic Four on fire with Human Torch on Fantastic Four.

Trophies.Title: Devourer of Worlds
Trophies.Description: Finish all the main missions and save the world on Fantastic Four.

Trophies.Title: Majority Leader
Trophies.Description: Have at least 5 allies with either Iron Man or Captain America on the Civil War table.

Trophies.Title: Unbreakable
Trophies.Description: Win a fight at Very Hard level: your opponent must have at least two more allies than you on the Civil War table.

Trophies.Title: Training
Trophies.Description: Earn your first rank by completing the clone training on the Clone Wars table.

Trophies.Title: Purge the World
Trophies.Description: Purge the galaxy by defeating both Sith Lords on the Clone Wars table!

Trophies.Description: Keep playing hard, and earn a score of at least 150 million on any table!

Trophies.Title: Pinball Pro
Trophies.Description: Flex your muscles and show off your pinball skills by earning 2000 Pro Score!

Trophies.Title: Pinball Alliance
Trophies.Description: Get your friends together and earn 10000 Team Score!

Trophies.Title: Pinball Explorer
Trophies.Description: Discover your collection, and play on at least 4 different tables!

Trophies.Title: From the Depths of Despair
Trophies.Description: Perform a successful bang back with the Captain America ball. Perform a bang back by nudging the table at the right time as the ball heads down an outlane.

Trophies.Title: Assemble!
Trophies.Description: Assemble the Avengers and start the Wizard mode against Loki and his army.
